"A little humor to start your Monday!"


CHICAGO -


The war on terrorism took a strange and  sad turn

 Friday as airline officials at O'hare  refused to let a

 73 year old grandmother board her plane as she

 had in her possession two six-inch knitting needles.


Apparently authorities were worried that she might

knit an Afghan.
